title: For Sale:  AR 15 - Custom AR-15 w/ SPR Contour Barrel, .223 Wylde Chamber
postcontent:
Tastefully built and customized SPR-inspired AR-15 build. The philosophy behind this build was to keep the weight low without compromising on components critical to a precision build.

Barrel:
18-inch SPR profile barrel w/ .223 Wylde Chamber (i.e. can shoot both .223 and 5.56 safely), 1:7 twist. I believe it is from White Oak Armament.

Lower:
LMT (Lewis Machine and Tool) Lower Receiver with enhanced Mil-Spec Trigger (very crisp pull) and ambidextrous safety selector. LMT branded Ergo Grip that feels very comfortable in the hand. 

Upper:
Midwest Industries SS12 Gen 2 Free-float Handguard with top rail; Handguard and barrel have been color-matched and Cerakoted OD Green; Optional 3-inch rails (not shown) are included (one of the modular rails has a built-in QD sling attachment, if you prefer that style). 
Factory bipod stud and sling swivel pre-installed and ready for Harris-style bipod without the need for a separate expensive rail mount that will add extra weight to the fore-end. 

Stock:
B5 SOPMOD Bravo Buttstock. VERY good fit, no play on extension tube.

Misc:
BCM Gunfighter Charging Handle; YHM (Yankee Hill Machine) muzzle device; removable Troy ambi QD sling attachment (behind endplate).
Troy Flip-up Iron Sights.
Custom-engraved dust cover. Shows Gadsden snake with text "Don't Tread On Me" when closed; "This End Toward Enemy" with Arrow when open. If you prefer a more conservative look and less tongue-in-cheek humor, I can replace it with a  standard dust cover.

Bipod and optics are NOT included.

This is a very handsome rifle, but make no mistake - it's a serious work horse built from top-shelf parts, and it WILL shoot sub-MOA if you do your part.

It's best to feed this rifle heavier grain (~77) bullets for serious precision work.
If you're just plinking at 100 yards, she seems to love the cheap 55-grain Federal American Eagle .223.

Asking $1650 for the rifle only (i.e. bipod and scope not included). Price is negotiable, so make me an offer.

For more/better pictures, go here:
http://imgur.com/a/Tg4eL#5

title: For Sale/Trade:  ISD SSR-85C-2 AK-47 with extras mag/ammo
postcontent:
AK-47 with a 1.6mm stamped receiver, all other parts milled, all serial numbers matching, and a trigger job imported by Armory USA. The 1.6mm version of this rifle has not been imported for some time, as they have gone to the less expensive 1mm receiver. the barrel on the rifle is a heavy/thicker material than most AK barrels and it is chrome lined along with the gas piston. This gun has only had about 150 rounds put down the tube, and the only markings on the rifle are from the safety (which is par for any AK). The rifling is still very strong given the very small amount of use this gun has seen, so it is good to go without any modifications. The trigger has also been polished and refined so it is a very smooth pull and lighter than most AK's on the market. The trigger actually gives my Smith and Wesson AR15 a run for it's money with what feels like less than a 3.5lb pull. The receiver also has space for a double hook trigger group to be mounted as these slots are already cut into the frame.

Along with the rifle you will also get 2 steel 30 round magazines, 160 rounds of ammo with both FMJ and JHP, and an installed no-slip sling. I fired the 90 rounds one magazine at a time, and the rifle was cleaned after each range trip, even though that is not completely needed with an AK. Let me know what you're offer is and we can talk from there. Blue Book value shows this gun at 90% is worth $750, and since the only mark on the weapon is from the safety, I'd say it was closer to 96% at least. I'm selling for well under blue book value so I assure you I am not attempting to gouge anyone with my price. I'm also flexible so gimme an offer! For trades I'd like to get close to the blue book value of $785. For cash I'd accept $700 OBO. Trades plus cash will fall into the second category. I can be reached by clicking the contact seller button, or by text (preferred)/call to 770-549-596three.
